      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Of course, I can help you with that! You are looking for the straight-line depreciation, which is the most common method for this type of problem. The formula is: (Cost - Salvage Value) / Useful Life.\n\nPlugging in your numbers: (50,000 - 5,000) / 5 = 45,000 / 5 = 9,000.\n\nSo, the annual depreciation is **9,000**.\n\nHere is the breakdown:\n1.  **Cost**: 50,000\n2.  **Less Salvage Value**: -5,000\n3.  **Depreciable Base**: 45,000\n4.  **Divide by Useful Life (5 years)**: 9,000 per year.\n\nLet me know if you need the calculation for a different method, like double-declining balance!",
